    <h4 class="media-heading">Cybertrust</h4>
    <p>
    	Phishing is a multi-billion-dollar problem that affects millions of web users daily. Malicious phishing content comes in many forms including targeted and untargeted email, websites that emulate the look and feel of legitimate sites, and social media posts. While spam filters and other technical measures prevent a lot of phishing campaigns from reaching their targets, many millions of phishing emails and social media posts make it to their potential victims daily â€“ putting the onus of phishing prevention into the hands of the end user. Fundamental research to accurately understand user behavior in making problematic trust decisions must be coupled with application development to bring awareness to users and reduce phishing victimization.<br>
