<p>
	Cybertrust is a simulation platform for conducting phishing research experiments. The platform was originally designed while I was at the University of Tulsa. CyberTrust presents users with realistic web content (both malicious and innocuous), helps researchers investigate how they perceive and trust different types of content, and then trains them to perform better in the future. <br>
    <br>
    Using the platform, we developed a phishing victimization prediction model based on structural indicators of trust that pinpointed the effects of different cues on victimization potential and showed that it could successfully predict victimization for youthful populations of users (18-25 demographic) based on an empirical study involving 80 subjects and over 5400 trust decisions.
